doc.para:
Math.RandomGenerator class Math.RandomGenerator is a class for generating random numbers by the Mersenne Twister method. The syntax of the constructor is as follows.
new Math.RandomGenerator([<Random seed>]);
Specifying a number in the constructor initializes the random number generator with that number. If you specify a dictionary array object that saves its state with the serialize method in the constructor, you can create a random number generator in that state. If the constructor is omitted, the random number generator is initialized with a random value based on the current time. (In the case of Kirikiri 2, it is initialized with a random number from the random number generator based on environmental noise instead of the current time. ).
